local-11.body:
Implemented shared-root DevNexus-Pharo setup in commit ceaa017 and published @evref-bl/dev-nexus-pharo@0.1.0-alpha.1 with npm dist-tag dogfood.

What changed:
- upgraded to @evref-bl/dev-nexus@0.1.0-alpha.7 so generic shared project configs without legacy kanban validate;
- project skills refresh now materializes DevNexus-Pharo plugin-declared skills, including MCP-Pharo skills, into .dev-nexus/skills and configured agent skill dirs;
- Codex init now detects shared DevNexus roots with the DevNexus-Pharo plugin and writes dev_nexus, dev_nexus_pharo, plexus_project, pharo_launcher, and pharo entries while removing old managed plexus/vibe_kanban entries;
- no live images, PLexus services, Docker, or Pharo Launcher processes are started by static setup.

Verification:
- npm run check in the DevNexus-Pharo worktree: 20 files / 184 tests passed.
- npm run check in the source checkout after fast-forward: 20 files / 184 tests passed.
- temp shared-project smoke: skills refresh installed 21/21 expected skills and codex init produced the five shared-root MCP entries.
